  "notes": "Self-contained development of the formal logarithm (Silverman IV.5): defines log_F as the integral of ω_F, builds a coefficient-by-coefficient compositional inverse (compInverse/compInverseOfUnit), proves the identity subst (compInverse f) f = X, and then proves Silverman IV.5.2 (log preserves addition) by a derivative + uniqueness argument using F.invariantDiff_translation and torsion-freeness. No sorries, no maxHeartbeats bumps; the longest proofs (coeff_add_monomial_pow_eq at 137 lines, coeff_subst_zero_X1_at_single_1 at 101 lines) are verbose binomial/finsupp calculations that could be golfed."
